Usage
	airclickd </dev/hidrawN

Notes
	Requires Linux '/dev/hidraw':
		Device Drivers -> HID Devices -> Generic HID support -> /dev/hidraw raw HID device support.

	Create executables in the PATH to be run on key press:
		airclick-play
		airclick-prev
		airclick-next
		airclick-voldown
		airclick-volup
	(Environment variables can be used to distinguish multiple daemons.)
